To this experiment, the fluorescence mode was observed in order to probe the Cpf. On increasing the concentration of Cpf from 0.0 to 1.0 μg/mL, the fluorescence intensity of JQDs + ATCh + AChE + DTNB increases, as shown in Fig. 7
                        a. As shown in Fig. 7b, the linear range was observed in the concentration range from 0.02 to 0.18 μg/mL and correlation coefficient (R2) 0.993. The measured detection limit was 2.7 ng/mL, with signal to noise ratio of 3 (S/N = 3), which is very low limit of detection compared to another published literature (Table 1
                        ). Therefore, the result indicates that the fluorescent detection of Cpfis simple, convenient and ultrasensitive.
